Merge pull request #125 from phyrwork/main

Improve waiting for subprocess-based services to start

commit.message:
Improve waiting for subprocess-based services to start.

Use an asyncio.wait_for timeout instead of retrying a fixed number
of times and use an exponential back-off between retries.

Also catch HTTP connection errors when checking the service state
as sometime we do the check before the remote server has had time
to start listening.

Also make service state check interval configurable and pass this
and timeout options up to subprocess-based Service()
implementations.

At timeout raise an ArsenicError instead of a generic Exception so
that applications can catch these errors better and decide what to
do next.

commit.message: add doc, fix for IE
add window_type arg and update tests
add new window call

Negative results from WebDriver are not Errors

...or put another way, correctly transporting errors is not itself
an error.

For example, in many test situations the most likely message traffic
between Arsenic and WebDriver will be "NoSuchElement" as test
implementations sit in wait_for_element() polling loops.  These
exceptions are mischaracterized as "errors," resulting in noisy log
output--and confusion.

Logging all exceptions that occur also results in double-logging,
since responses are already logged.
